task.summary: Default task
changed bes and res file extensions
added yahtzee example
finished parity game creation, also 2 and a half player games without (co)product and truncated (co)sum)
added more examples
paritygames can now be reduced
fixed parity game printing
fixed parity game reduction for current examples
paritygames can now be created from RESs
added a label operator to allow checking for average values (see yahtzee example)
added time measurements
added a way of creating a RES that only creates equations that are necessary for the solution (local)
added an argument that allows to compute the average running time over a number of runs
in case of multiple runs, individual times are shown too
slight print change
altered res file name to store locally created RESs separately
added more examples
Altered the locality option for RES creation such that it is now a post processing step on top of the original RES creation, maintaining the original order
altered solveres to accommodate the changes of the last commit
fixed makeRESlocal and added test example
added and altered some yahtzee examples
added proper parse support for (multiple) action parameters
reimplemented local RES creation as something instead of non-local RES creation
removed print statements
implemented use of dependency graph
local RES creation now properly simplifies right hand sides
when the dependency graph is used for substitutions it no longer substitutes into equations that have already been processed
improved removing worse operands from maximum similarly to as how it was recently improved for minimum
reorganised examples from mCRL2 tool-set and added one
added a solving method that traverses the dependency graph recursively and fixed removing dependencies
increased loss probability of brp models
fixed some initialisations, added tarjan.py
renamed order to SCC in most places, removed SolveRESDep, createLocalRES can now divide the equations in blocks
